    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-11-30T19:08:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-11-30T19:08:00-05:00" n="628"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                <head>628. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d628fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 684A.86/11–2356. Confidential. Drafted by Gamon (<gloss
                            target="#t_IO1">IO</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss>), cleared
                        by <persName corresp="#p_RWM1">Rountree</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_PH1">Phleger</persName>, and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_WFO1">Wilcox</persName> who signed for <persName
                            corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-11-30T19:08:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1956—7:08 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>384. Re <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 176.<note n="2" xml:id="d628fn2"
                        >In <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 176, <persName
                            corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> reported that <persName
                            corresp="#p_MG1">Meir</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_EA1"
                            >Eban</persName> had advised him that a complete Israeli withdrawal
                        would only mean a renewal of the blockade and Israeli troops facing Egyptian
                        troops on the old Armistice lines and a renewal of the buildup of Soviet war
                        potential in the Sinai area. They said that if <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                            >U.N.</gloss> troops followed an Israeli withdrawal, that was another
                        matter, but they had not received assurances from the United States that
                        that was what was contemplated. <persName corresp="#p_MG1">Meir</persName>
                        and <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eban</persName> asked to be advised of the
                        U.S. position. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.)</note> Re Palestine. You
                    should inform Mrs. <persName corresp="#p_MG1">Meir</persName> that we believe
                    Israel should comply with <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> resolution and
                    withdraw its forces from Egyptian territory and behind Armistice Line. In US
                    view this should be accomplished without conditions and without delay. Questions
                    such as blockade and build-up of Soviet arms while serious in themselves and
                    requiring close attention should not affect Israel’s compliance with <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> resolution. In addition you may <pb facs="1272"
                        n="1232" xml:id="pg_1232"/> inform her we appreciate and will bear in mind
                    concern of Israeli Government that Sinai, Tiran Straits islands, and Gaza not be
                    permitted revert automatically to bases for Egyptian military action against
                    Israel. You should make it clear to Mrs. <persName corresp="#p_MG1"
                        >Meir</persName> that US fully supports the position being taken by <gloss
                        target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> regarding withdrawal of Israeli forces.</p>
                <p>Memorandum <persName corresp="#p_WFO1">Wilcox</persName>–<persName
                        corresp="#p_SR1">Shiloah</persName> conversation Nov. 28<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d628fn3">Not printed. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.,
                        684A.86/11–2856)</note> touching on above being pouched.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
